🧠 OS Concept 1: File System Basics
1️⃣ Simple Idea

File System =
👉 way OS stores and organizes data on disk

🧠 Real-World Analogy

Think of your college file cabinet 📁

Files → documents
Folders → subjects
Structure → organization
⚙️ Why It Exists

Without file system:

❌ Data scattered randomly
❌ No structure
❌ Hard to access

⚙️ Key Concepts
1️⃣ File

Collection of data

Example:

notes.txt
2️⃣ Directory

Folder that holds files

Documents/
   ├── notes.txt
   ├── code.c
3️⃣ Path

Location of file

/home/user/docs/file.txt
4️⃣ File Operations
create
read
write
delete
🔗 Connection to OS

OS manages:

file storage
permissions
access
🎯 Placement Question

Q: What is a file system?

👉 A method used by OS to store, organize, and access files on disk.

🧠 Memory Trick
File System = Organized storage
🧠 OS Concept 2: Disk Scheduling

🔥 VERY COMMON QUESTION

1️⃣ Simple Idea

Disk Scheduling =
👉 deciding which disk request to serve first

🧠 Real-World Analogy

Lift (elevator) 🛗

People press buttons:

2nd floor
5th floor
1st floor

Lift decides order → optimize movement

⚙️ Why It Exists

Disk is slow ❌
Movement takes time

Goal:

👉 minimize seek time

⚙️ Algorithms
1️⃣ FCFS

Serve in order

✔ simple
❌ slow

2️⃣ SSTF (Shortest Seek Time First)

👉 nearest request first

✔ faster
❌ starvation possible

3️⃣ SCAN (Elevator) 🔥

👉 moves in one direction

✔ practical
✔ widely used

🔗 Connection to Scheduling (Day 3)

Similar to CPU scheduling:

👉 but for disk

🎯 Placement Question

Q: Why SCAN is better than FCFS?

👉 reduces total movement and improves efficiency

🧠 Memory Trick
Disk = Elevator problem
⚙️ COA Concept 3: Cache Coherence
1️⃣ Simple Idea

Cache Coherence =
👉 keeping data consistent across multiple caches

🧠 Real-World Analogy

Group project 📚

If one student updates answer:

👉 all must have same version

⚙️ Why It Exists

In multi-core systems:

each core has its own cache
data may become inconsistent
⚙️ Example
Core1 → updates X = 10
Core2 → still has X = 5

❌ wrong result

⚙️ Solution

Protocols ensure:

👉 all caches updated correctly

🔗 Connection to Parallel Processing (Day 10)

Multi-core → need coherence

🎯 Placement Question

Q: What is cache coherence?

👉 Maintaining consistency of data across multiple caches.

🧠 Memory Trick
Coherence = Same data everywhere
⚙️ COA Concept 4: Memory Consistency
1️⃣ Simple Idea

Memory Consistency =
👉 order in which memory operations appear to execute

🧠 Real-World Analogy

WhatsApp messages 💬

Order matters:

"Send money"
"Don’t send money"

Wrong order → disaster

⚙️ Why It Exists

In parallel systems:

👉 operations may reorder

⚙️ Key Idea

Ensure:

👉 all processors see operations in correct order

🔗 Connection to Cache Coherence
Coherence → same value
Consistency → correct order
🎯 Placement Question

Q: Difference between coherence and consistency?

👉 Coherence = same data
👉 Consistency = correct order

🧠 Memory Trick
Coherence = Same value
Consistency = Same order
